wiki.content: “TE MUDASTE” is a romantic reggaeton with lonely vibes, featuring producers Bad Bunny had never collaborated with: Caleb Calloway and Mr. Naisgai. The beat changes completely at the end of the song, becoming an instrumental outro that incorporates elements of synthwave and retro 80s pop. Through the lyrics, Bad Bunny is recounting the feelings of nostalgia that he feels when thinking about an ex-partner that he had. This nostalgia evokes towards him when looking at the photos of her with her and when thinking about moments like sex, the walks together and the first times they were intimate. As the subject progresses, Benito is curious to know what will become of her and is excited by the possibility of having something together again. Read more on Last.fm.
